<F P=103> BK2303102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 23 (KPL) -- Mr. Khamphoui 
Keoboualapha, deputy prime minister, president of the Committee 
for Planning and Cooperation, yesterday, received the visiting 
delegation of the Association of Journalists of Thailand led by 
its president, Mr. Pramot Fai-upala. 
  The Lao deputy prime minister, as he welcomed the Thai 
journalists, said that he was pleased to see that journalists of 
the two neighbours had established links for mutual benefits 
which would enable the sides to exchange professional 
experiences. Better understanding among journalists could also 
be instrumental for the consolidation of the relations of 
friendship and cooperation between the two nations. 
  The discussion between Mr. Khamphoui Keoboualapha and his 
Thai guests passed in an atmosphere of friendship. Mr. Bouaban 
Volakhoun, acting president of the Journalists' Association of 
Laos, also deputy minister of information and culture, 
accompanied the Thai journalists to see the deputy prime 
minister. 
  During the visit from March 21-27, apart from Vientiane, the 
Thai journalists are scheduled to visit northern Luang Prabang 
Province. The Journalists' Association of Thailand presented the 
Journalists' Association of Laos 50,000 bahts [Thai currency]. 

