<H3> <TI>   IAEA Director Speaks at 24 Mar UN Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2303234294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2100 GMT 23 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2303234294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Cha Man-sun, from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] Director 
General Hans Blix will participate in the unofficial UN Security 
Council [UNSC] on the afternoon of 24 March to give an oral 
report on the results of North Korea's inspection and on the 
details of how the IAEA Board of Governors came to adopt a 
resolution against North Korea. 
  At the meeting, Director General Hans Blix will express deep 
regret over the fact that North Korea's nuclear issue has fallen 
into a deadlocked situation due to North Korea's uncooperative 
measures and will emphasize that strong measures at the UN 
Security Council level are unavoidable. The IAEA will refrain 
from taking independent action regarding future inspections on 
North Korea, but will act upon the UNSC's countermeasures. 

