<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agricultural Cooperative Group Elects President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403065794 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD in English 24 Mar 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403065794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Won Chol-hui was elected chairman of the National 
Agricultural Cooperative Federation (NACF) for a four-year term 
yesterday. 
  Won, 56, took over the chairmanship of the NACF by earning 
875 of the 1,386 votes cast directly by regional cooperatives 
heads at the NACF auditorium. 
  Won, an executive vice president of the NACF, competed with 
two other candidates, Chong Ki-su and Chong Tae-kun, who 
garnered 162 and 345 votes, respectively. 
  The new NACF head assumes the chairmanship today as the 
second NACF to be selected chosen directly by federation 
deputies. 
  Won succeeds Han Ho-son, who is now under arrest on charges 
of embezzlement. Han resigned from the post last Saturday. 
  "I will push ahead with drastic reforms to transform the 
NACF 
into a "genuine" body which will serve farmers and will develop 
new projects," the new chairman said in a news conference 
shortly after the election. 

</TEXT>

