<F P=103> BK2403163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 24 -- General Secretary Do Muoi and 
his entourage arrived in Kuala Lumpur, this morning beginning 
his official friendship visit to Malaysia as guest of Prime 
Minister Mohamed. Mr Do Muoi was welcomed at the airport by 
Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi and accompanied Minister 
Daud Taha. 
  After the official welcomed ceremony held in the 
Parliamentary Square, General Secretary Do Muoi and Prime 
Minister Mahathir Mohamed reviewed the honour guards of 
Malaysian armed forces. Mr. Mahathir Mohamed introduced Mr Do 
Muoi the Malaysian Government's officials. Among those present 
at the event on the Malaysian side were Deputy Prime Minister 
Anwar Ibrahim, Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi, Cabinet 
Minister Abang Abu Bakar Mustapha, and Defence Minister Najib 
Tun Razak. Vietnamese Ambassador to Malaysia Ngo Tat To and 
members of diplomatic corps attended the ceremony. 

