<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA Official Begins Five-Day Working Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2403161694 Hanoi VNA in English 1427 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2403161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 24 -- Dr. Sueo Machi, deputy 
director general of the International Atomic Energy Agency 
(IAEA) concluded today his five-day working visit to Vietnam. 
  While here Dr. Machi and Prof. Nguyen Dinm Tu, director of 
the National Institute of Nuclear Energy (NINE) exchanged views 
on activities of IAEA and NINE and the application of nuclear 
technology in agriculture, industry, health care and 
environmental protection. 
  Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam, received Dr Machi on March 
20. During the reception Dr Machi highlighted the close 
cooperation of the Vietnamese Government in implementing 
projects funded by IAEA. He also expressed his hope that in the 
future, nuclear technology will be widely applied in various 
economic branches in Vietnam, especially in agriculture. 
  For his part, Minister Nguyen Manh Cam thanked IAEA for its 
aid to Vietnam through technological assistance projects and 
expressed Vietnam's concern about the promotion of cooperation 
between IAEA and Vietnam in the use of nuclear energy for peace 
purpose. 
  Dr Machi visited sub-institutes of the National Institute of 
Nuclear Energy in Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City and Da Lat. 

</TEXT>

