<H3> <TI>   SRV's Do Muoi Arrives for Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2403080094 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2403080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vietnam's political leader, Do Muoi, arrived in 
Kuala Lumpur today for a four-day official visit aimed at 
intensifying bilateral and economic relations between Kuala 
Lumpur and Hanoi. The 77-year old Secretary General of Vietnam's 
Communist Party was met on arrival at the airport by Foreign 
Minister Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi. 
  Accompanied by a 33-member delegation including politicians, 
businessmen, and journalists, Do Moui is scheduled to meet Datuk 
Sri Dr. Mahathir for talks on bilateral, regional, and 
international issues in the afternoon. 
  During his stay here he will attend a briefing at the 
Petronas [National Petroleum Corporation] headquarters and tour 
refineries in Melaka. He will also visit the Proton automobile 
plant in Shah Alam, near Kuala Lumpur. 

