<H3> <TI>   Delegates Present Proposals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2503104094 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 0630 GMT 25 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2503104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The plenary session of the National Convention 
continued at 0900 this morning in the Central Meeting Hall of 
president's residence compound on Ahlone Road, Yangon [Rangoon]. 
  The plenary session was attended by the chairman of the 
National Convention Convening Commission, Lieutenant General Myo 
Nyunt; the vice chairmen, Lt. Gen. Maung Thint and Brigadier 
General Myo Thant, and commission members; the chairman of the 
National Convention Convening Work Committee [NCCWC], U Aung 
Toe; the vice chairman, U Tha Tun, and work committee members; 
the chairman of the management committee, Brig. Gen. Tin Aye, 
and committee members; delegates; and local and foreign 
correspondents. 
  At the plenary session, U San Tha Aung of the Mro or Khami 
National Solidarity Organization acted as the acting chairman; 
Dr. Than Nyunt, Daw May Than Lwin, U Mahn Ohn Maung, U Kan 
Nyunt, U Soe Maung, U Tin Maung, U Khin Maung Htoo, and U Sai 
Aung Htun participated in the panel. U Khin Maung Myint, 
director general of the Office of the NCCWC and in charge of the 
meeting, acted as master of ceremonies. 
  First, the master of ceremonies announced that 663 out of 
694 
delegates attended the meeting and declared the session 
successful. 
  According to the agenda, the delegates from the delegate 
group representing other invitees read proposals to report their 
fundamental principles related to the state, state structure, 
and head of state chapters that will be included in drawing up 
the constitution. 
  U Saw Hla Tun from Sagaing Division and Dr. Han Saw of the 
Mandalay Institute of Medicine read the proposal paper 
collectively prepared by the delegate group representing other 
invitees; (U Mahn Ko Gaung Khun) read the proposal paper 
belonging to the delegate group representing the invitees from 
Special Region-1, Kachin State; and (U Gabel Byan) read the 
proposal paper belonging to the delegate group representing 
other invitees from Kayan Group. Afterwards, the plenary 
session recessed at 1100. The afternoon session of the National 
Convention plenary session is continuing in the Central Meeting 
Hall of the president's residence compound on Ahlone Road, 
Yangon. 

</TEXT>

