<F P=100> INTER-ASIAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on PECC General Meeting </TI></H3>
<H4>   Do Muoi on ASEAN Membership </H4>
<F P=102> BK2403161494 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in Malay 
1300 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2403161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Malay </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vietnam said it will join ASEAN only when its 
membership in the grouping benefits all ASEAN and Vietnam. Do 
Muoi, the general secretary of the Vietnam Communist Party, said 
this at a question and answer session with participants of the 
10th general meeting of the Pacific Economic Cooperation 
Council, PECC, in Kuala Lumpur this evening. He said Vietnam is 
currently studying the ASEAN working mechanism and will join the 
group when the situation is right. Mr. Do Muoi also said that 
ASEAN can contribute greatly to the rebuilding and modernization 
of Vietnam. He pointed out ASEAN can contribute to the economic 
well-being of Vietnam, especially in terms of technology. He 
hoped ASEAN member countries will invest more in Vietnam. 
  Malaysia is currently the 10th largest investor in Vietnam 
with a total investment of 400 million U.S. dollars. 
  When asked for Vietnam's opinion on the dispute over the 
Spratly Islands, Mr. Do Muoi said that all parties concerned in 
the claim to the islands should resort to action that will not 
raise tension in the region. He reiterated that the issue 
should be resolved either through bilateral or multilateral 
meetings. 

</TEXT>

