<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rescue Squad Finds Missing UK Soldiers Alive </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2503083994 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0645 GMT 25 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2503083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, March 25 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- The five 
British soldiers who went missing on Mount Kinabalu, Southeast 
Asia's highest peak in the east Malaysian Sabah State, are alive 
and were spotted Friday by a Royal Malaysian Air Force 
helicopter combing the area. 
  The group, missing since March 8, was sighted at 10.10 am 
about 15 km from Nalangkap Nahandang Village, Captain Mohamed 
Affendie Mohamed Hanafi of the Defence Ministry's Public 
Relations Unit said. 
  Another helicopter with a rescue squad, including several 
members of a British search and rescue team was immediately sent 
to the area. 

</TEXT>

