<H3> <TI>   Trade Union Group Blasts ROK on Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403153594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1518 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of 
Korea in a statement today bitterly denounced the Kim Yong-sam 
group's dangerous criminal acts to provoke a nuclear war in 
conspiracy with outside forces as a heinous treachery to plunge 
the Korean nation into a nuclear scourge. 
  The statement says: 
  "The South Korean authorities are heading for reckless 
confrontation with fellow countrymen, totally denying 
North-South dialogue. This is an extension of the anti-DPRK, 
anti-socialist campaign they have consistently waged with the 
imperialist reactionaries. 
  "No sooner had they brought the working-level contact for 
the 
exchange of presidential envoys to a rupture than they kicked up 
a big fuss as a servant of foreign forces in the anti-DPRK, 
anti-socialist campaign, by issuing a `special alert order' 
throughout South Korea, calling their master on the phone, 
sending a letter to him and making mendicant trips to do harm to 
fellow countrymen. 
  "The reality shows that with the flunkeyist traitor left 
within the nation, our fellow countrymen cannot live in peace 
nor can they think of the peace and peaceful reunification of 
the country and the nation will inevitably suffer a scourge of 
war. 
  "We regard it humiliating to have the traitor within the 
nation. We will never tolerate his treacheries. 
  "The traitor Kim Yong-sam must clearly know that he will 
never be able to escape the blame for the consequences of his 
dependence on outside forces and flunkeyism against fellow 
countrymen." 

</TEXT>

