<F P=103> SK2403124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- A national contest of 
workers art circles was held in Pyongyang from March 14 to 23 to 
significantly celebrate the birthday of the great leader 
President Kim Il-song. 
  Put on the stage of the contest were more than 650 pieces of 
colorful numbers, including instrumental music and song, dance 
and story-telling, which had been created by working people at 
factories and enterprises across the country through their brisk 
art activities, upholding the policy of the Workers' Party of 
Korea on popularizing art activity. 
  Among them were a poem and song tale "The Love and 
Benevolence Will Be Conveyed Forever", a choral poem recitation 
and story-telling "Great Might of Korea", a female vocal solo 
and mixed vocal homophony "The Whole World Envies", a choral 
poem recitation and story-telling "Let Us Carry Through Party's 
Revolutionary Economic Strategy". They well showed the 
greatness, wise leadership and noble communist virtues of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il, the great pride and honor of the working class of 
chuche Korea and the happy life and worthwhile labour of the 
Korean working people. 

