<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increase in Smuggling, Drug Trafficking Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2503053694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2503053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The KINH DOANH VA PHAP LUAT (Business and Law) 
journal has recently reported that goods smuggling has been 
increasing since early this year. Concerned agencies recently 
detected two of out a group of eight foreign cargo ships 
carrying smuggled goods. 
  Drug trafficking has also been on the increase in recent 
days. In the first two months of this year, the authorities 
uncovered 17 cases of trafficking and confiscated 450 kg of 
opium and 0.72 kg of heroin. The most serious was the smuggling 
of 129 kg of opium by cadres of the Dien Bien goldsmith shop in 
Lai Chau Province. 
  It is noteworthy that the manufacturing and trading of fake 
goods done in meticulous ways are also widespread. Police 
nationwide have so far detected and dealt with 2,700 cases. 
This is a new challenge for responsible agencies in the 
struggle against smuggling. 

</TEXT>

