<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Wartime System' Reportedly Assumed by DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2503064194 Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO in Korean 25 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2503064194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sin Tong-chae] </F>
  [Text] It has been learned that all of North Korea has 
entered a wartime system and an emergency order [pisangryong] 
was handed out to the whole Army. 
  Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae and Kim Tok, director of the 
Agency for National Security Planning, reported this to Prime 
Minister Yi Hoe-chang during a security-related ministers' 
meeting held at the prime minister's official residence on 25 
March. They revealed that North Korea has suspended issuing 
travel permission to its residents and is heightening an 
atmosphere of willingness for war [iljon pulsa punwigi]. 
  According to the report, the North Korean Army intensified 
military exercises and examined its emergency communications 
network. It has also increased construction of defense 
facilities, including installing barriers. Meanwhile, North 
Korean media, including radio broadcasts, claim that "a 
Southward war is inevitable." [taenam chonjaengi pulgapi hada] 
  According to this, Prime Minister Yi instructed relevant 
ministers that a crisis management system should be concretely 
worked out to cope with an emergency and this system should be 
thoroughly examined. 

</TEXT>

