<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Security-Related Ministers Meet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2503102994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1020 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2503102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, march 25 (YONHAP) -- Security-related 
ministers met at the prime minister's residence at Samchong-tong 
Friday to review the country's security conditions at a time 
when President Kim Yong-sam is out of the country making 
official visits to Japan and China. 
  Prime minister Yi Hoe-chang asked those present at the 
meeting to be more vigilant against the dogmatic adventurism of 
North Korea. 
  "You should be prepared against any eventuality as the North 
Korean nuclear question is about to come away from the stage of 
dialogue into the phase of sanction by the UN Security Council," 
Yi said. 
  The prime minister also suggested that relevant offices let 
the people fully know about the government's policies toward 
North Korea since he said the people's understanding is 
important in building up the nation's overall security 
preparedness. 
  The officials present at the meeting included, besides the 
premier, Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu, Defense Minister Yi 
Pyong-tae, Information Minister O In-hwan, NSP Director Kim Tok 
and Chief Presidential Secretary Pak Kwan-yong. 

</TEXT>

