<H3> <TI>   Communique Further Details Capture of Pailin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2403142294 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2403142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique of the Khmer Royal Armed Forces General Staff on </F>
additional results in the total capture of Pailin area; dated 24 
March -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] After totally capturing Pailin area on 19 March, 
the Khmer Royal Armed Forces [KRAF] swept up those who 
obstinately refused to lay down their weapons and return to 
national society. 
  While launching the sweep operation in Pailin City, the KRAF 
made an appeal and gave an assurance in line with the national 
reconciliation policy of the Royal Government of the Kingdom of 
Cambodia, which stresses: 
  1. The Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] still recognizes 
all compatriots as Cambodian citizens like all innocent 
Cambodians in general who are currently living with the RGC. 
The RGC always cares about the fate of all compatriots. 
  2. The RGC guarantees its recognition of the ownership of 
land, houses, and all other property that the compatriots 
possess currently in line with the provisions of the existing 
laws of the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  But, the obstinate Khmer Rouge ringleaders did not heed this 
appeal. They instead launched attacks against the KRAF. In the 
combat for self-defense, the KRAF killed 35 hardheaded Khmer 
Rouge elements on the spot; seized a tank, 453 assorted guns, 70 
metric tons of assorted ammunition, dozens of tons of war 
materiel, two bulldozers, a Toyota car, a 751-A cistern, (?a 
jeep), and 80-meter radio antenna. 
  [Signed] General Pan Thai for the KRAF General Staff 
  Issued on 24 March 1994 

</TEXT>

