<H3> <TI>   ROK President Kim Continues Speeches, Meetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Discusses `Sea of Fire' Comment </H4>
<F P=102> SK2503133794 Seoul KBS-1 Television Network in Korean 1210 
GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2503133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Kim Yong-sam, meeting with ROK 
correspondents in Tokyo this morning, said that the remark made 
by the North Korean delegate at the inter-Korean working contact 
held last week threatening that North Korea is ready for war was 
premeditated and that he regards it as the remark of the highest 
person in authority in North Korea. 
  President Kim Yong-sam said that he thinks China basically 
does not want North Korea to develop nuclear weapons since China 
does not want to be isolated as a member of international 
community. President Kim said that he will be able to have frank 
exchange of views with Chinese President Jiang Zemin through 
summit talks with him on the measures to cope with the critical 
North Korean nuclear issue. 

