<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Ends Visit to Finland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2503093094 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2503093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Suphachai Phanitchaphak has 
concluded an official visit to Finland successfully. During the 
visit, during 17 to 20 March 1994, the deputy prime minister 
paid a courtesy call on Prime Minister Esko Aho and had 
consultations with Deputy Prime Minister [title as heard] (Kari 
Hopanatti) and Finnish business leaders as well as members of 
Finland-ASEAN Society. On trade cooperation, the two sides 
expressed satisfaction with rapid increase in trade between the 
two countries. Thailand asked Finland to increase imports from 
Thailand and give Thailand generalized system of preferences, or 
GSP. Both countries emphasized a new role of trading gateways 
to Indochina, Commonwealth of Independent States, and Russia. 
  During the visit, the two countries signed an agreement for 
investment promotion and protection. Thailand wants Finland to 
make direct investment in Thailand without going through a third 
country. Finland agreed to send experts to help Thailand on 
science and technology. It also asked to increase flight 
frequency to Bangkok to cope with tourist demand. 

</TEXT>

