<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai Bank Expects Higher Economic Growth Rate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2503064394 Bangkok THAI RAT in Thai 25 Mar 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> BK2503064394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THAI RAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Tharin Nimmanhemin yesterday 
reported on the country's economic, capital, and financial 
markets to Prime Minister Chuan Likphai. During the meeting, he 
told the prime minister that the country's economy is 
progressing in a good direction. Some past problems have been 
tackled well. The Bank of Thailand is readjusting its economic 
growth forecast from 7.8 percent to 8 percent, an increase of 
0.2 percent. The growth rate is considered quite high. The new 
adjustment is likely to be announced in April. 
  Meanhwile, Tharin also said he has informed the prime 
minister that IMF officials would come to study and assess the 
Thai economy. The officials are specifically interested in the 
country's policy on wealth distribution to rural areas because 
they believe that Thailand has implemented such measures 
effectively. The IMF officials want clear a explanation of the 
policy so that it can be used as a guideline for conducting the 
study. 

</TEXT>

