<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims `Mature Enough' for Leadership Change </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2503023294 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0000 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2503023294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense and Security Minister Edi Sudrajat and 
Religious Affairs Minister Tarmizi Taher say religious believers 
are are currently mature enough to face a leadership succession. 
Speaking during a news conference yesterday, the defense and 
security minister said national resilience, particularly in the 
face of the leadership succession, is in good condition and 
there is no situation that may lead to an upheaval. According 
to Minister Edi Sudrajat, national resilience must be 
consistently enhanced. Thus, the defense and security minister 
called on all parties to continue to enhance national resilience. 
  Meanwhile, Religious Affairs Minister Tarmizi Taher said the 
fact that Muslim scholars had directly asked the head of state 
about the leadership succession is proof of the high degree of 
their concern. In addition, the Muslim scholars hope that 
everything will proceed constitutionally for the sake of all 
Muslims. 

</TEXT>

