Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at a news conference on 27 March, Foreign 
Minister Tsutomu Hata commented on countermeasures Japan will 
take if the UN Security Council decides to impose economic 
sanctions against North Korea over the issue of suspected 
development of nuclear weapons, and said: "We would like to 
take responsible measures to deal with the situation as a member 
of the United Nations should the UN show us some kind of 
direction." In this way, he stressed a view that Japan will act 
in accordance with the UN decision. 

