<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Reviews Press for 24 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2403144994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1338 GMT 24 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2403144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 24 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
newspaper "ARDIYN ERH" informs that the spring session of the 
Great State Hural of Mongolia has completed the consideration in 
first reading of the regulations of the research centre to be 
founded under the jurisdiction of the parliament. The draft 
regulations were drawn up by a special commission. The 
newspaper notes that the research centre under the parliament is 
intended to carry out research work promoting the improvement of 
the draft laws being elaborated and to provide the Great State 
Hural with information required. According to the newspaper, 
the session has charged the standing parliamentary committee on 
meetings and adminstration to work out within the April month 
for submitting for consideration to the Great State Hural the 
proposals on setting up a working group to provide making 
changes and am endments to the election law. The newspaper 
reports that the chairman of the great state Hural N. Bagabandi 
congratulated the population of the country of Kazah descent on 
the occasion of their conventional spring holiday "Nauryz". 
  The "ARDIYN ERH" informs that on the invitation of the 
deputy 
prime minister of the state council, Minister of Foreign Affairs 
of the People's Republic of China Qian Qichen, the Minister of 
External Relations of Mongolia T. Gombosuren would pay an 
official visit to China. The visit is to last from 6 to 11 
April. 
  The newspaper carries an article by chairman of the 
subcommittee of the Great State Hural on struggle with bribery 
and abuses of official position M. Zenee. In the article it is 
stressed that it is the spread of corruption which is the major 
reason hampering the progressive development of any state. M. 
Zenee believes that over a few last years the tendency towards 
widespreading of the corruption and abuses of official position 
is being observed to be characteristic of a number of 
representatives of high-ranking state authority bodies including 
a member of the parliament R. Gonchigdorj. The capital 
newspaper "ULAANBAATAR" continues publishing materials devoted 
to the forthcoming 355th anniversary of the city. In this issue 
the newspaper writes about the creation at the end of the 30s a 
thermo power station in Ulaanbaatar. 
  Such a power station was built under assistance of a German 
AEG firm with the participation of German and Swedish engineers. 
The newspaper underlines that the power station was installed 
with the most modern for that time equipment made in such 
countries as Britain, Germany and Sweden. The power station was 
put into operation in the autumn of 1931. 
  In his article published in the newspaper an academician T. 
Dabaajamts puts forward his ideas aimed at improving the 
conventional Mongolian dwelling ger. [as received] According to 
the academician, the ger is of not so least importance for 
solving the housing problem of the population. 
  The newspaper gives an inverview with the head of the 
veterinary service of the capital D. Baljinnyam who noted that 
according to the results of the census there are more than 266 
thousand head of privately owned cattle. D. Baljinnyam said 
that the vaccination of the cattle population is started in the 
city. 
  He expresses his anxiety about the growing number of stray 
dogs in the capital regarding them to be impeding a serious 
danger for both the residents of the city and the population of 
cattle as well. 
  According to the newspaper, on the initiative of a group 
youth [as received] in the Mongolian capital there has been 
created the first fan club named after the well known rocksinger 
from Great Britain Elton John. 
  Members of the club are planning to celebrate the birthday 
of 
the singer who will be 47 tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

