<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tourist Visas Extended To Stimulate Economy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2603164094 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 26 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2603164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In order to speed development of the Myanmar 
[Burma] hotel and tourism industry, to enhance the economy 
through the hotels and tourism industry, and to welcome tourists 
to Myanmar, which is rich in tradition, cultural heritage, and 
nature, the Ministry of Hotels and Tourism has been finding ways 
and means to develop its activities quickly. 
  Thus, with the view to attract more tourists, the duration 
of 
entry visas for tourists has been increased from two weeks to 
four weeks and the foreign exchange requirement has been 
increased to US$300 from US$200. These changes have been 
effective since 14 March. 

</TEXT>

