<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dissident Zargana Released From Prison </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2603142094 Hong Kong AFP in English 0628 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2603142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rangoon, March 26 (AFP) -- Burma's best-known 
comedian, Zargana, has been released after four years in prison 
as a political dissident, neighbors of his family said Saturday. 
  Zargana, 33, who trained as a dentist but turned to comedy, 
gained prominence for his satirical jokes aimed at the former 
socialist regime. 
  First arrested briefly as a political dissident in late 
1988, 
he went to jail for the second time in 1990 while helping his 
mother in her campaign for the May general elections that year. 
  Neighbors who spoke to Zargana on Friday said he had been 
delivered to his parents' home by military intelligence 
personnel just before noon. 
  He was the latest political prisoner released by the 
military 
junta, known as the State Law and Order Restoration Council 
(SLORC), which has set free more than 2,000 dissidents in the 
past two years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

