<H3> <TI>   Mahathir Positive on Relations With SRV </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2603131594 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2603131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir, says 
bilateral relations and cooperation between Malaysia and Vietnam 
over the past few years have brought positive results to be 
proud of. Bilateral trade between the two countries, which 
stood at 235.4 million ringgit in 1991, had increased to 473 
million ringgit in the first nine months of last year. Speaking 
at a dinner hosted for the visiting general secretary of the 
Communist Party of Vietnam, Mr. Do Muoi, in Kuala lumpur last 
night, Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir said many Malaysian companies had 
ventured in Vietnam. As such, the Vietnamese Government should 
give consideration to these companies, which should help in its 
economic growth, by further awarding them projects. He also 
pointed out that Southeast Asian countries should resolve 
problems among themselves in a peaceful manner while cooperating 
with each other to bring about mutual benefit. Everyone must 
realize the dream of a peaceful, stable, and united Southeast 
Asian region. 

</TEXT>

