<H3> <TI>   ROK's Kim, Delegation Conclude Meetings, Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Delegation Departs Tokyo for PRC </H4>
<F P=102> OW2603040394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0354 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2603040394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 26 KYODO -- South Korean President Kim 
Yong-sam departed from Tokyo's Haneda airport on Saturday [26 
March] for China where he will meet Chinese leaders to discuss 
North Korea's alleged nuclear arms program and Seoul's growing 
trade ties with Beijing. 
  Kim and his wife Son Myong-sun concluded a three-day visit 
to 
Tokyo where the South Korean president urged joint efforts to 
persuade Pyongyang to give up its nuclear ambitions and stressed 
the importance of future-oriented bilateral relations. 

</TEXT>

