  [Text] Tokyo, March 24 KYODO -- The first regular air 
service between the northern Japan port city of Hakodate and 
Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk, capital of Sakhalin in the Russian Far East, 
will start April 4, Transport Ministry officials said Thursday 
[24 March]. 
  The date was set when the ministry gave the go-ahead 
