<H3> <TI>   LDP To Send Loan Investigators to Kumamoto </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2603124594 Tokyo NHK General Television Network in 
Japanese 1000 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2603124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NHK General Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from the "NHK News 7" </F>
  program] 
  [Text] The Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] held a meeting 
this afternoon of its special committee investigating Prime 
Minister Morihiro Hosokawa's 100 million-yen loan from the 
Sagawa Kyubin parcel delivery group. In the meeting, the 
committee decided to send its members to Kumamoto Prefecture 
next week to investigate whether any illegal transactions took 
place when the prefectural government authorized the 
construction of a major resort facility at the foot of Mt. Aso 
during Hosokawa's term as Kumamoto governor. 
  At today's meeting, the committee discussed ways to promote 
investigation from now on. Noting that Kumamoto prefectural 
government changed its regulations when it authorized the 
construction of a resort facility near Mt. Aso during Hosokawa's 
term as governor, the members agreed that this move was unusual 
and should be investigated. 
  The committee decided to send four members, including 
Committee Chairman Matsunaga, who is former international trade 
and industry minister, to Kumamoto on 31 March. The four will 
interview prefectural officials about details of the regulation 
changes and visit the resort facility in question. 

</TEXT>

