<H3> <TI>   Agreement Signed With Sweden on Double Taxation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2703064994 Hanoi VNA in English 1420 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2703064994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 26 -- Vietnamese Ambassador to 
Sweden Pham Ngoc, on behalf of the Vietnamese Government, and 
Vice Minister of Finance Dick Kling, on behalf on the Swedish 
Government, signed in Stockholm on March 24 an agreement on 
avoidance of double taxation between the two countries. 
  Together with the agreement on investment promotion and 
guarantee signed in September 1993, the new agreement will 
contribute to promoting their economic, commercial, 
scientific-technical and investment cooperation on the basis of 
mutual benefit in conformity with the traditional friendship and 
cooperation between the two countries. 

