<F P=106> ["Foolish Act To Frighten DPRK With Strength" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- U.S. Defence 
Secretary Perry declared on March 24 that if the United Nations 
Security Council decided to take "sanctions" against North 
Korea, the United States would send additional troops and 
weapons to South Korea, according to a report from Washington. 
  The South Korean paper CHOSUN ILBO March 25 quoted "U.S. 
military sources" as saying that a plan was being worked out by 
the U.S. military to hurl 600,000-strong military strength 
including two marine divisions, more than 200 warships, over 
1,600 planes, etc. to the Korean peninsula from the U.S. 
mainland within 80 days in "case of emergency." 
  Meanwhile, U.S. Deputy Undersecretary of Defence Slocombe 
said on March 24 that a U.S. carrier task fleet was in "full 
readiness for action" to cope with "a possible contingency" on 
the Korean peninsula and the mobilization system of the U.S. 
imperialist aggression forces in South Korea was under 
reexamination. 
  Facts show that the U.S. warmaniacs are rendering the 
situation of the Korean peninsula extremely strained. But their 
attempt to frighten the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 
with strength is really a foolish act. 
  Our people and People's Army want peace but are never afraid 
of war. 
  The U.S. imperialists would be well advised to act with 
discretion and stop running riot with proper knowledge of Korea. 
  Our people and People's Army, who are united closely around 
the party and the leader, are keenly watching the military moves 
of the U.S. imperialists. 

