  The news analyst says: 
  Recently, Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa said 
"suspected nuclear programme of North Korea causes great concern 
in the international community." And Japanese Foreign Minister 
Tsutomu Hata blared that "if North Korea refuses inspection or 
takes an irresolute attitude, Japan will show a stern response." 
  This is a reversed logic defending the criminal posing a 
