imperialist reactionaries. 
  The Japanese authorities' phraseology about "sanctions" and 
"stern response" to the DPRK shows that they are looking for a 
chance to launch an anti-DPRK military action with the nuclear 
issue as a pretext. 
  The Japanese reactionaries, dreaming of repeating the 
history 
of aggression, regard the Korean peninsula as the first target 
in their overseas expansion. 
  If the situation on the Korean peninsula goes worse and a 
war 
breaks out, Japan will never be safe, either. 
  The reckless military action of the Japanese reactionaries 
against the Korean people will result in digging their own grave. 

