Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["The United States Must Act With Discretion" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- A very grave situation 
fraught with danger of war has been created on the Korean 
peninsula. 
  The United States and the South Korean puppet clique are 
openly crying that they would resume the provocative "Team 
Spirit" joint military exercises and have decided to deploy 
"Patriot" missiles in South Korea. Now fleets of aircraft 
carriers of the U.S. Navy are moving toward the waters close to 
Korea. 
  Synchronizing with this, the South Korean puppet Army has 
been put on a "standby posture" on the order of the traitor Kim 
Yong-sam and the puppet Joint Chiefs of Staff issued a "special 
emergency order" to all the puppet Army. 
  These provocative moves are very dangerous developments 
which 
may cause a catastrophic crisis on the Korean peninsula. 
  The perfidious act of the United States in totally reversing 
the agreed conclusions reached at the DPRK-U.S. contact in New 
York is the factor driving the situation on the Korean peninsula 
to the brink of war. 
  Raising unreasonable preconditions to us who have honestly 
implemented the points of its agreement with the U.S., the 
United States manipulated the Board of Governors of the 
International Atomic Energy Agency at its meeting to adopt an 
unjustifiable "resolution" against us. Worse still, it is 
trying to introduce "sanctions" against us at the United Nations 
Security Council. 
  The seditious forces of the United States are posing a grave 
military threat to us, letting loose a string of very 
provocative belligerent outbursts that the "international 
community must take tough measures", and it "must increase 
pressure on North Korea by practical acts." 
  The acts of the United States in bringing the situation to 
extremes after reversing the agreed conclusions in New York and 
making the DPRK-U.S. talks abortive will never produce results 
favourable to it. 
  The United States had better look squarely at the 
seriousness 
of the present situation and ponder it over and must stop the 
reckless row of pressure and adventurous war moves at once. 

</TEXT>

