<H3> <TI>   Radio Warns of `Catastrophic Crisis' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603060094 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0407 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2603060094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0407 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A very grave situation involving a danger of war 
[chonjaeng wihomul naepohan maeu omjunghan chongse] is being 
created on the Korean peninsula. 
  The United States and the South Korean puppet clique are 
openly saying that they will resume the provocative Team Spirit 
joint military exercise. They have decided to deploy Patriot 
missiles to South Korea and are finally planning to send 
additional U.S. troops to South Korea. In addition, U.S. Navy 
aircraft carriers are now moving toward waters near our country. 
  Amid these circumstances, the South Korean puppet Armed 
Forces have been put on a state of alert at traitor Kim 
Yong-sam's order, and the puppet Joint Chiefs of Staff ordered 
the entire puppet military forces to be put on special alert. 
  Seoul is scheming war plots [chonjaeng mouidul] every day. 
These very unusual, provocative moves that can be seen only just 
prior to an adventurous [mohomjogin] war are an extremely 
dangerous development that may cause a catastrophic crisis 
[pagukchok wigirul choraehalsu innun kukhi wihomchonmanhan satae 
palchon] on the Korean peninsula. 
  The insidious forces [pulsun seryoktul] of the United States 
are making extremely provocative warmaniac outbursts [kukhi 
tobalchogin chonjaeng pogondul], such as remarks that the 
international community must take strong measures, that pressure 
on North Korea must be strengthened by actual steps, that North 
Korea must not misunderstand the U.S. intent, and the like, 
posing military threats against us. 
  All these facts plainly show that the United States is not 
interested in resolving the nuclear issue of the Korean 
peninsula and is only trying frantically to isolate and stifle 
[apsal] our republic. 

</TEXT>

