  [Text] Pyongyang, March 27 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
comments on the ever more intensified interference in and 
suppression of the press by the "Security Planning Board" (SPB) 
[Agency for National Security and Planning -- "NSP"] in South 
Korea. 
  The "SPB" not only strictly bans the press from reporting 
about the mounting struggle on South Korean people against the 
flunkeyist treacheries of the traitorous Kim Yong-sam clique and 
its confrontational row against the North, their anti-American 
and anti-fascist struggle for democracy and their anti-war and 
anti-nuke struggle but also manipulates the subsidized media to 
mislead public opinion over the "nuclear issue of the North", 
the news analyst of the paper says, and continues: 
  The tightened control on the press by the Kim Yong-sam group 
through the "SPB" is unthinkable apart from the crisis of the 
"civilian government". What the puppets pursue in suppressing 
the press is to bar it from digging up and opening to the public 
their anti-national crimes and curb the anti-"government" action 
of the people. 
  It is a symptom of the end of the "civilian government" to 
try to maintain the treacherous rule by blindfolding the people 
and stuffing their ears and mouths through the suppression of 
the press. 
  The further the puppets intensify their anti-DPRK smear 
campaign and suppression of the people and the press through the 
"Security Planning Board", the fiercer the struggle of the 
people grows against the "civilian" dictatorship. 

</TEXT>

