<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Warmaniacs' in South Accused of Acting Rashly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803055294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0512 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803055294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 28 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
"prime minister," Yi Hoe-chang, at a "roundtable conversation of 
security-related ministers" on March 25 cried for a 
"high-intensity alert posture against the North", a "perfect 
posture for countermove" and the like and, on the 26th, turned 
up at frontline units of the puppet Army and whipped up an 
extreme war fever, drivelling that they should be in a full 
defence posture to cope with an "emergency", according to a 
radio report from Seoul. 
  Meanwhile, the puppet Army held a "plenary meeting of staff 
officers" on March 26 and discussed the question of doing their 
utmost to maintain a posture for immediate entry into action". 
Such moves are unpardonable criminal acts leading the situation 
on the Korean peninsula to the brink of a war. 
  All the developments cleary show that the South Korean 
bellicose elements do not want peace and peaceful reunification 
of the country but have used the North-South dialogue to gratify 
their sinister aim of putting the brakes on the DPRK-U.S. talks. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group can by no means conceal the fact that 
it is an anti-national group blocking the dialogue between the 
fellow countrymen and trying to inflict the scourge of war upon 
the nation with the help of outside forces. 
  The "civilian" warmaniacs must stop acting rashly, clearly 
mindful of what bitter results their war frenzy would bring to 
them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

