<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Described as `Brilliant Commander' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803052494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0459 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 28 (KCNA) -- The song "We Will Win 
Because You Are Leading Us" is widely sung among the Korean 
people. 
  The poem of the song was written by Ni In-mo, the 
incarnation 
of faith and will. It represents the unshakable idea that the 
cause of socialism is invincible as long as it is guided by the 
Dear Leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The Korean people are firmly defending the cause of 
socialism, holding General Kim Chong-il, the great iron-willed 
brilliant commander, in high esteem as supreme commander of the 
Korean People's Army. 
  General Kim Chong-il is a great military genius endowed by 
nature with the resourcefulness and personality of a brilliant 
commander. 
  Possessed of flawless quality and traits of an iron-willed 
brilliant commander and ever-victorious military strategist, he 
has strengthened the people's army and increased the might of 
socialism to be invincible with his unrivalled military 
intelligence, matchless grit and distinguished commanding art. 
Under his guidance today the Korean People's Army has grown 
into ever-victorious revolutionary armed forces equipped with 
modern offensive and defensive means and the entire people have 
been armed and the whole country has been fortified. 
  The Dear Leader is a great brilliant commander who is 
possessed of iron will not shaken by any roar of thunder. 
  Whenever the situation was carried to the brink of war in 
Korea by the aggressive war moves of the U.S. imperialists, he 
dealt a bitter defeat to the enemy in the spirit of decisive and 
fierce attack, without a moment's hesitation and vacilation. 
When the U.S. imperialists and their stooges ran riot last year 
to stifle the DPRK, resuming the frantic team spirit joint 
military exercises and demanding "a special inspection" of it, 
the supreme commander instantly proclaimed a semi-war state and 
powerfully aroused the whole party, the whole country and the 
entire people in defending the dignity and sovereignty of the 
country and the nation. 
  Now the U.S. imperialists are rendering the situation of the 
Korean peninsula extremely strained, after massively bringing to 
the Korean peninsula and its surroundings new-type fighter 
planes, warships and other means of nuclear strike of different 
types and Patriot missiles, totally reversing the agreed 
conclusions reached at the DPRK-U.S. contact in New York. 
  The United States is trying to bring the Korean people to 
their knees with a strong arm and pressure. But it is a mistake. 
  Nobody is equal to the strength of the singlehearted unity 
of 
the Korean people rallied closely behind the great brilliant 
commander. 

</TEXT>

