<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Extends Thanks to War Veterans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803055494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0502 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803055494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 28 (KCNA) -- The Dear Leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il extended thanks to 47 war veterans 
including Mun Song-gyun, participants in the past Fatherland 
Liberation War, in the Hwayang co-op farm, 14 veteran party 
members including Chu Tong-yun, head of the sub-workteam of 
veteran party members in the Nyongpho co-op farm in Chongdan 
county, 11 veteran party members of the 13th party cell of 
Kangnyong county seat households including Han Thae- il, and a 
farmer Sin Nyon-yong at the workteam No. 6 of the Songwol co-op 
farm in Ongjin county, who helped boost the production of grain, 
in south Hwanghae Province. 
  Out of the desire to live up to the loving care of the party 
and the state, they have cultivated lands to do farming and 
produced a large amount of rice. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il also sent thanks to a worker Choe 
Song-gol of the Kwangdok mine and a worker Kang Hi-chun of the 
Ni Yong-rok enterprise, who rescued five children from the 
danger of drowning. 
  To devote individuals to the society, the collective and 
revolutionary comrades has become a social trend in the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 

</TEXT>

