<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Attend National Tree-Planting Ceremony </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603053594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0436 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2603053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- A national 
tree-planting ceremony was held here Friday on the lapse of 47 
years since the great leader President Kim Il-song planted trees 
on Munsu Hill in Pyongyang and on the lapse of 37 years since 
the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il planted trees on Chang Hill 
in the city. 
  Present at the ceremony were Pak Song-chol, Politburo member 
of the C.C. [Central Committee], the Workers' Party of Korea 
[WPK] and vice-president; Kim Chung-nin, secretary of the WPK 
Central Committee; and Kim Pok-sin, vice-premier of the 
Administration Council. 
  Chu Song-il, chairman of the C.C., the General Federation of 
Trade Unions of Korea, made a report there which was followed by 
speeches. 
  The reporter and speakers recalled that President Kim 
Il-song 
opened up a broad vista for land development, indicating the 
orientation, ways and tasks for reforestation and wisely led the 
work to carry them into practice. 
  They also noted that Comrade Kim Chong-il instituted tree- 
planting day and tree-planting months to convert afforestation 
into a nationwide work and called for a brisk movement of 
tree-planting on a mass scale. As a result, mountains and 
fields of the country are covered with green forests and the 
cities and countryside have changed their appearance, looking 
more beautiful, they added. 
  They referred to the task to create in the next few years 
200,000 hectares of forests of oil-bearing trees and 200,000 
hectares of forests of trees for industrial use. 
  After the ceremony the participants and working people 
planted hundreds of thousands of trees on Munsu and Chang hills 
and in Nungna islet, the Taesongsan holiday resort, Kwangbok 
street and other places to make the capital city of Pyongyang 
more beautiful and covered with more luxuriant verdure. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

