<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Publication of Science, Technology Books Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403231694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1513 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403231694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- Publishing houses of 
Korea have recently brought out many new books of science and 
technology. 
  "Interpretation of Heat Conduction by Midget Computer" 
published by the science and encyclopedia press group consists 
of three parts and nine chapters which explain the method of 
solving equations of heat conduction with programs. The press 
group also printed "Medicinal Tea and Health and Longevity". 
The book gives general knowledge of medicinal tea and describes 
its kinds, making and drinking, and introduces tonic tea, tea 
for recovering fatigue and teas for treating diseases. 
  The agriculture publishing house brought out "Comprehensive 
Mechanization of Agriculture", "Artificial Insemination of 
Domestic Animals and Technology", "Soil Dictionary" and other 
books conducive to widening the technical knowledge of 
agricultural officials. 

</TEXT>

