<H3> <TI>   Keating Appeals for Calm Over FYROM Recognition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2803030494 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0100 GMT 
28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2803030494 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Australian Government has again appealed for 
calm in the continuing row over its recognition of the Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM]. In a statement read to 
crowds of people celebrating Greek independence day, Prime 
Minister Paul Keating expressed regrets that Australia's good 
record of harmonious community relations were under threat. He 
urged ethnic and religious leaders to appeal for calm and to 
resolve differences lawfully. 
  There have been a number of arson attacks on shops and 
churches and by members of both communities. 

</TEXT>

