<H3> <TI>   Closer Ties With Singaporean Forces Agreed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2803123594 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2803123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Singapore and Australia have signed a letter of 
intent promoting closer ties between the armed forces of the two 
countries. It was signed by the defense minister, Dr. Yeo Ning 
Hong, and his Australian counterpart Senator Robert Ray in 
Canberra. 
  Mindef [Ministry of Defense] says the two armed forces will 
explore ways of extending and enhancing reciprocal activities, 
exchanges, and cooperation for mutual benefit. 
  Dr. Yeo is in Australia on a four-day official visit at the 
invitation of Senator Ray. He held discussions with Senator Ray 
and the minister for trade and acting foreign minister, Senator 
Bob McMullan. Dr. Yeo also called on the Australian prime 
minister, Mr. Paul Keating. 
  He is accompanied on the visit by the minister of state for 
finance and communications, Commodore Teo Chee Hean. 

</TEXT>

