<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Paper Hails Country's Achievements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2703111094 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2703111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Russian newspaper on 24 March carried an article 
hailing the achievements made in various fields by the Lao 
People's Democratic Republic [LPDR], especially in economic 
development. The newspaper pointed this out in particular 
following the recent visit to Russia by Somsavat Lengsavat, LPDR 
foreign affairs minister. 
  The newspaper said that the relations between Russia and 
Laos 
at the governmental level was suspended for some time. But now 
these relations have been restored. It noted: Russian Foreign 
Affairs Minister Andrey Kozyrev and Lao Foreign Affaires 
Minister Somsavat Lengsat held talks in Moscow in early March. 
As a result of the talks, in addition to revitalizing past 
relations, the two sides also signed a treaty on fundamental 
relations and an agreement on cultural, scientific, and 
technical cooperation between the two countries. The paper went 
on to say that implementing an open-door policy and mechanisms 
of the market economy, Laos achieved peace and development. 
This policy has brought self-sufficiency in food supply and 
monetary stability to Laos and has reduced its inflation rate to 
only between 5 and 10 percent. Comprehensive changes in the 
social sector have also contributed to bolstering Laos' economic 
relations with other countries. Laos is currently utilizing 
foreign investment to build the infrastructure and to expand 
communications routes to the neighboring countries, namely 
Vietnam and Thailand. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

