<F P=102>  BK2603143794 Vientiane KPL in English 0820 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2603143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 26 (KPL) -- The Nordic Development 
Fund (NDF) has signed here an agreement to release a U.S. $6.5 
million loan to Laos' communication sector. 
  The loan is to be used in the construction of nine new 
bridges on Road 13-south between the ferry point to Pakkading. 
The Swedish International Development Authority (SIDA), in this 
connection, also agreed to give a grant of six million kronas 
for hiring experts to supervise the construction of the bridges. 
  The signing of the agreement was done following the review 
of 
the cooperation in the field by SIDA mission and the Lao 
Ministry of Communication, Transport, Post and Construction 
[CTPC] carried out recently. Signing the memorandum of 
understanding were Mr. Khamlouat Sitlakon, deputy minister of 
CTPC and the charge d'affaires of Sweden to Laos, Mr. Rolf 
Carlman. 

