<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Envoy to France on Possible UN Sanctions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603010794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0041 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2603010794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 26 (YONHAP) -- The representative of 
the North Korean general mission in Paris, Pak Tong-chun, 
commenting on possible U.N. sanctions against his country, says 
Pyongyang is prepared to go to war or resume dialogue on the 
nuclear issue. 
  In an interview with the daily LIBERATION, Pak said Thursday 
that the Korean peninsula is at "a negative turning point." 
  If the United States and its allies including France imposed 
economic and other sanctions, North Korea would regard it as a 
declaration of war, Pak said. 
  "As North Korea is ready to wage an all-out war, it is also 
ready to resume dialogue," he said. "This is not just idle talk." 
  He also threatened that a "catastrophic situation" would 
develop on the Korean peninsula if the United States and South 
Korea resumed their annual military exercise Team Spirit. 
  "Dialogue is always possible," Pak stressed, "but Team 
Spirit 
will have to be cancelled before it can take place." 
  U.N. sanctions against North Korea or deployment of Patriot 
anti-missile missiles in South Korea could force Pyongyang to 
withdraw from the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-7382 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas059_d_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-059 </AU>
