<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Reaction to Russian 8-Party Proposal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603035294 Seoul HANGYORE SINMUN in Korean 26 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2603035294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul HANGYORE SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has reacted negatively to the 
Russian Government's proposal for an eight-party conference made 
up of the four powers involved in the Korean peninsula issue, 
North and South Korea, the UN secretary general, and the 
International Atomic Energy Agency director-general in order to 
smoothly resolve the North Korean nuclear issue. 
  On 25 March, a relevant Foreign Ministry official indirectly 
refused the Russian Government's proposal, saying: "We believe 
we need to prudently review the proposal for the conference, 
which will include relevant countries, such as the United States 
and Japan, on the North Korean nuclear issue. It is more 
important, however, to be patient because the UN Security 
Council is now discussing the North Korean nuclear issue." 
  The official said that "the Russian Government had already 
informed the ROK Embassy in Russia of its intention to make the 
proposal before it was announced internationally." He added 
that "the Russian Government's proposal was likely made to 
resolve the North Korean nuclear issue, which has been recently 
deadlocked, through a multilateral approach." 

</TEXT>

